 <para id="fs-idm31815696"><newline/><emphasis effect="italics">Use the following information to answer the next three exercises:</emphasis> The standard deviation of heights for students in a school is 0.81. A random sample of 50 students is taken, and the standard deviation of heights of the sample is 0.96. A researcher in charge of the study believes the standard deviation of heights for the school is greater than 0.81.</para><exercise id="eip-412"><problem id="eip-222">
