  </exercise><para id="eip-717"><newline/><emphasis effect="italics">Use the following information to answer the next four exercises:</emphasis> The average waiting time in a doctor’s office varies. The standard deviation of waiting times in a doctor’s office is 3.4 minutes. A random sample of 30 patients in the doctor’s office has a standard deviation of waiting times of 4.1 minutes. One doctor believes the variance of waiting times is greater than originally thought.</para><exercise id="eip-608">
   <problem id="eip-638">
  <para id="eip-974">What type of test should be used?</para>
